			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yep, you can.  But it's dangerous and you need a lot of room.  I learned this method in NK... I would think that RM would be too cramped.  SoW is way better than jboots, btw, and at least initially, you'll want to have sow cast on you.<br><br>Make sure you have pet taunt off.  If you can, have a druid cast sow on your pet as well.  If not, use expedience.<br><br>Take your best bolt, face away from the giant at max range, and cast.  Immediately, cast again.  By the time that the first bolt arrives your second one should be done casting.  Start running, and send your pet in.<br><br>Now, the tricky part is to be able to use the 3rd person camera view to see when the HG turns on your pet.  Stop, immediately cast your bolt again, and a second one if he doesn't immediately turn back to you.  Keep doing this until he comes after you.  Run like hell again, and try to stay out of his range.<br><br>Once you get this trick down, you can kite quite a few things that are slightly bigger than what you could normally take down.  I used to run around Seafury island with a group of 6-8 cycs in tow, with my water pet backstabbing along.  :-) <p></p><i></i><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=502692&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Zashir Swiftpaw</span></a> -- Savage Lord
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171313&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Eloina Pyromancer</span></a> -- Arch Mage <span style="font-style: italic">[Retired]</span>
