			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is a mana-intensive alternative for HGs for a good white-knuckle fight at 39.<br><br>First, Summon a focused fire pet, BOII, Expedience, Tiny Companion (I swear that spell makes my pet last longer!)platemail, 2 swords.  Make sure he casts his DS before pulling!!<br><br>On me - KEI, Greater Shielding, Phantom Plate, Spirit of Wolf.  Ring for fast casting, bracelet for power nukes, earring for low cost nukes.<br><br>Spell lineup - 1. Blaze  2.  Shock of Spikes  3.  Shock of Blades  4.  Malaise  5. 29 Earth pet (fast cast just in case) 6. Renew Summoning  7.  Renew Elements  8.  Gate<br><br>Pick a single HG, because adds will kill you fast.  I grabbed one from the eastern part of West Karana.  Pull with Malaise, and send pet in.  When the pet is at 80%, begin to chain heal starting with renew summoning.  The recast delay sucks on both spells, but you can cast one while the other refreshes.  You will be able to keep the pets health up pretty well, but it will lose probably 1-4% per round.  Some rounds the HG will miss or hit for low damage.  When you see this, cast Shock of Spikes (speed is the key here), then immediately resume chain healing.  When you feel brave or feel the fight is going well, stick Shock of Swords in the heal rotation.  Every little bit of damage helps, and it casts very fast.  Using this, I was able to keep the pet up above 50% health, and take small chunks out of Mr. Giant.  He turned to run at 14%, so then use Blaze and finish him off.  Varn had 37% health at the end, and I had 33m.  Never got aggro or considered chaining a decoy.<br><br>Not efficient for xp, not a proven tactic, but damn fun. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
