			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK, you can easily take out a hill giant.  I was in Rathe yesterday with my lvl 40 mage partnering with a lvl 36 enchanter.  When she left, I decided to take a single pop solo, and it was almost too easy.<br><br><br>First, I know many folks love the fire pet.  Time to put it away and get out a focused air pet.  I think you can buy it at 39 and you can easily buy all the items for the Broom of Trilon at the bazaar (although everyone should suffer hours of Najena hell like I did).<br><br>Next, give it a set of Phantom Plate, an elemental defender, and 2 swords.  WHAT A DIFFERENCE!  Once when I did not equip a pet to fight (focused fire), the Hill Giant was hitting for 96 damage or more.  After the armor, the damage moved in the 70s-80s and lower.  Burnout II and Barrier of Combustion.  Send pet in and malaise.<br><br>The glory of the air pet over fire is the agility.  It simply was not getting hit.  Fire and Earth take pretty serious beatings vs. HGs, and you end up spending all the time healing the pet.  The air pet dropped below 80% once.  He probably could have solo'd it.<br><br>Watch the pet damage, and nuke after he taunts.  3 or 4 cinder bolts will do him in.  Maybe a shock of spikes at the end to keep him from running.<br><br>After that, I stayed and tried the same tactic with 2 more HGs.  It was just easy.  My only problem was frikin dr00ds trying to ks everything in the rathe mtn zone.  I learned that if you pull with malaise, you WILL get ks'd (some crap about no damage, no claim), but if you pull with Cinder Bolt, dr00ds don't have a chance.  If they rooted, I would just use it to my advantage and cinder bolt from max range.  Wait til it is dead and they shout to zone about a ks, and watch every mage, wizard, and necro collectively shout &quot;boo frikin hoo, ya stupid dr00d!&quot;  Well worth it in sheer satisfaction.  Get SoW potions or Jboots just in case you get a little too much aggro.  At 96 damage per hit vs. a 39 dress-wearing mage (about 800hp?), you won't last 15 seconds.<br><br>Spell line up:  1. Cinder Bolt  2.  Shock of Spikes  3.  Fire Bolt (low aggro damage pull)  4.  Malaise  5.  Burnout II  6.  Renew Summoning  7.  Renew Elements  8.  Gate <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A> at: 1/21/03 6:16:10 pm<br></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
